<div id="community-vibe">
    <h2 class="sect-title">Community Vibe in Mission </h2>
    <div class="col-grid-2">
        <div>
            <p class="par-lg">Running right down the middle of Mission is 4th Street, home to a selection of
                restaurants, shopping and public services.</p>
            <p class="par-xl">Mission has become a popular area for restaurants, with over 35 on 4th street alone and a
                majority having patio space for summer use.</p>
            <p class="par-lg">Unique restaurants range from the more gourmet foods, such as Mercato International
                restaurant and market offering the best quality Italian food, to the more quick bites from 4th Street
                Pizza to Burger Inn. Nightlife on 4th is also popular, from the local Joyce on 4th Pub to Wurst, a
                Bavarian themed Beer Hall. 17th Avenue is one of Calgary’s most popular areas for entertainment and
                shopping. Nellies Cosmic Café is a popular breakfast and brunch destination for it’s good food and
                friendly service. The night is booming with the assortment of pubs, bars and clubs along the length of
                17th Avenue, including Republik Nightclub, host to a selection of DJ’s every Friday with no cover
                charge.</p>

            <p class="par-lg">Talisman Centre, formerly Lindsey Park, is located in Mission and is a popular
                multi-sports complex, with summer camps available beginning in July and events held year round for
                various different celebrations. Across McLeod Trail is the Calgary Stampede Grounds, home to the annual
                Calgary Stampede every July, which attracts over a million visitors from around the world and presents a
                great deal of entertainment, from music, to rodeo to performances to the most magnificent Canadian
                artwork.</p>
        </div>
